          <!-- 10. Cookies -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-bold mb-4">10. Cookie Policy and Digital Tracking Technologies</h2>
            <p class="text-foreground leading-relaxed">To ensure the security, efficiency, and continuous optimisation of our digital platforms, SPVH Group utilises cookies, web beacons, cryptographic tokens, and similar tracking technologies. This section outlines our operational mechanics regarding digital telemetry and your rights in managing these technologies.</p>

            <h3 class="text-dark text-lg font-bold mb-3 mt-6">10.1. What Are Cookies?</h3>
            <p class="text-foreground leading-relaxed">Cookies are small, encrypted text files placed on your device (computer, tablet, or smartphone) by your web browser when you visit our public websites or log into our secure client portals. They act as a memory mechanism, allowing our servers to recognise your device, authenticate your session, and recall your specific regional or platform preferences.</p>

            <h3 class="text-dark text-lg font-bold mb-3 mt-6">10.2. Categories of Technologies We Deploy</h3>
            <p class="text-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We deploy digital tracking technologies strictly to enhance user experience, ensure platform security, and gather aggregated intelligence. We classify these into the following operational categories:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-foreground list-disc pl-5">
              <li><strong class="text-dark">Strictly Necessary (Essential) Cookies:</strong> These are foundational to our digital architecture. They are required to authenticate user logins into our secure vaults, manage encrypted sessions, and enforce our security firewalls. Because these are critical to the operation and security of our platforms, they cannot be disabled.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-dark">Performance and Analytical Cookies:</strong> These technologies collect aggregated, anonymised telemetry data regarding how visitors interact with our digital assets (e.g., tracking navigation paths across our Technology &amp; Research insights or measuring dwell time on our Automotive portfolio). We use enterprise-grade analytics partners to process this data, allowing us to optimise our digital infrastructure and content delivery.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-dark">Functional Cookies:</strong> These allow our platforms to remember bespoke choices you have made — such as language preferences, regional settings, or specific interface customisations — to provide a more frictionless, tailored digital experience upon your return.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-dark">Strategic Engagement (Targeting) Cookies:</strong> SPVH Group does not participate in mass-market, third-party advertising networks. However, we may use specific tracking tokens to deliver highly relevant corporate updates, sector-specific research, or invitations to proprietary engagements based on your previous interactions with our platform.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-dark text-lg font-bold mb-3 mt-6">10.3. Third-Party Analytics and Ecosystem Integrations</h3>
            <p class="text-foreground leading-relaxed">In addition to our proprietary cookies, we utilise vetted, institutional-grade third-party service providers (such as advanced web analytics and security-monitoring firms) who may place their own tracking technologies on your device when you interact with our ecosystem. These entities operate strictly as data processors under our mandate and are contractually bound by rigorous confidentiality agreements.</p>

            <h3 class="text-dark text-lg font-bold mb-3 mt-6">10.4. Consent and Control Mechanisms</h3>
            <p class="text-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We respect your digital sovereignty and provide mechanisms to control your tracking preferences:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-foreground list-disc pl-5">
              <li><strong class="text-dark">Initial Consent:</strong> Upon your first visit to our platforms from relevant jurisdictions, you will be presented with a compliance banner requesting explicit consent to deploy non-essential cookies.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-dark">Browser-Level Controls:</strong> You maintain the right to configure your web browser to refuse all cookies, selectively accept certain categories, or alert you when a cookie is being deployed.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-dark">Impact of Refusal:</strong> Please be advised that if you configure your browser to block Strictly Necessary cookies, you may experience degraded platform functionality, and you will be unable to access our authenticated client portals, digital vaults, or secure advisory dashboards.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

